criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients older than 18 years.

          2. Diagnosis of Temporal Lobe Epilepsy based on clinical, electrophysiological, magnetic
             resonance (MRI) and computed tomography (CT) imaging of the brain.

          3. Patients will be selected who are able to adequately complete the self-administered
             questionnaires and handle the home tDCS equipment.

          4. 13 points or more on the Beck Depression Inventory.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Clinical history suggestive of other paroxysmal abnormalities other than temporal lobe
             epilepsy, such as syncope, psychogenic seizures, or transient vascular accident;

          2. Change in the antiepileptic regime in the last 30 days;

          3. History of status epilepticus on last year;

          4. Performed vagus nerve stimulation (VNS), Deep Brain Stimulation (DBS) or other
             neurostimulation <1 year prior to study;

          5. Active suicide plane;

          6. Contraindication for tDCS, including head injury, metal on the head or any implanted
             medical device, including pacemakers and cardiac defibrillators;

          7. Pregnancy.
